## 2.2 Tenant Isolation Audit

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Every data table MUST have `business_id` for row-level tenant isolation.

| Model | Has `business_id` | Assessment |
|-------|-------------------|------------|
| products | ✅ | OK |
| customers | ✅ | OK |
| invoices | ✅ | OK |
| invoice_items | ✅ | OK |
| purchases | ✅ | OK |
| **purchase_items** | 🔴 **NO** | **CRITICAL: No tenant isolation** |
| **challan_items** | 🔴 **NO** | **CRITICAL: No tenant isolation** |
| **pos_transaction_items** | 🔴 **NO** | **CRITICAL: No tenant isolation** |
| **pos_payments** | 🔴 **NO** | **CRITICAL: No tenant isolation** |
| **pos_refund_items** | 🔴 **NO** | **CRITICAL: No tenant isolation** |
| **restaurant_order_items** | 🔴 **NO** | **CRITICAL: No tenant isolation** |
| **price_list_items** | 🔴 **NO** | **CRITICAL: No tenant isolation** |
| **credit_note_items** | 🔴 **NO** | **CRITICAL: No tenant isolation** |
| **campaign_messages** | 🔴 **NO** | **CRITICAL: No tenant isolation** |
| **segment_customers** | 🔴 **NO** | **CRITICAL: No tenant isolation** |
| **payroll_items** | 🔴 **NO** | **CRITICAL: No tenant isolation** |
| **promotion_products** | 🔴 **NO** | **CRITICAL: No tenant isolation** |

> [!CAUTION]
> **12 child/junction tables lack `business_id`**. While they are accessed via parent JOINs today, any direct query against these tables risks cross-tenant data leakage. This is a **fundamental multi-tenancy safety violation**.

## 2.3 Indexing Strategy Audit

| Area | Assessment | Details |
|------|-----------|---------|
| Primary Keys | ✅ UUIDs on all tables | Good for distributed systems |
| Foreign Keys | ✅ Present on all relations | Proper referential integrity |
| Business ID Indexes | ⚠️ Inconsistent | Some tables have composite [(business_id, ...)](file:///c:/Users/zaliz/Downloads/APP_CHAT/financial-hub/lib/services/InventoryService.js#22-27), others don't |
| GIN Indexes on `domain_data` | ✅ | Good for JSONB filtering |
| Date-range Indexes | ⚠️ Partial | `gl_entries` lacks [(business_id, transaction_date)](file:///c:/Users/zaliz/Downloads/APP_CHAT/financial-hub/lib/services/InventoryService.js#22-27) composite |
| Soft Delete Indexes | ✅ `is_deleted` indexed | Good for filtered queries |

### Missing Critical Indexes

```sql
-- gl_entries: Critical for accounting reports
CREATE INDEX idx_gl_entries_biz_date ON gl_entries (business_id, transaction_date);
CREATE INDEX idx_gl_entries_biz_account ON gl_entries (business_id, account_id);

-- pos_transactions: Critical for POS session reports
CREATE INDEX idx_pos_tx_session ON pos_transactions (session_id, created_at DESC);

-- product_stock_locations: Critical for warehouse queries
CREATE INDEX idx_psl_biz_warehouse ON product_stock_locations (business_id, warehouse_id);

-- payments: Missing business_id + date composite
CREATE INDEX idx_payments_biz_date ON payments (business_id, payment_date DESC);
```

## 2.4 Audit Trail Compliance

| Field | Coverage | Assessment |
|-------|----------|-----------|
| `created_at` | ✅ All tables | Good |
| `updated_at` | ⚠️ Most tables | Missing on `gl_entries`, `pos_payments` |
| `created_by` | 🔴 Most tables | Only `journal_entries` has it |
| `updated_by` | 🔴 No tables | **MISSING everywhere** |
| `is_deleted` / `deleted_at` | ⚠️ Some tables | Products, invoices, customers — but NOT purchases line items |

> [!WARNING]
> Financial tables (`gl_entries`, `journal_entries`) lack `updated_by` tracking. For SOX/audit compliance, every financial record modification must track WHO made the change.

## 2.5 Financial Precision

| Aspect | Implementation | Assessment |
|--------|---------------|------------|
| Decimal Precision | `Decimal(12, 2)` on all amounts | ✅ Good for currency |
| Exchange Rate Precision | `Decimal(18, 8)` | ✅ Excellent |
| Tax Rate Precision | `Decimal(5, 2)` | ✅ Good |
| JS Calculation | `Math.round(x * 100) / 100` | ⚠️ Floating-point risk at high volumes |

> [!TIP]
> Consider using integer-based cents arithmetic in JS (multiply by 100, operate on integers, divide at display) to eliminate floating-point errors entirely.

