> [!CAUTION]
> **The vast majority of server actions do NOT enforce RBAC permissions.** They only check authentication and business membership. This means any authenticated business member (even a `viewer`) can create invoices, modify accounting entries, process POS transactions, etc. The [withGuard()](file:///c:/Users/zaliz/Downloads/APP_CHAT/financial-hub/lib/rbac/serverGuard.js#31-172) system exists but is **not uniformly adopted**.

## 3.3 Response Structure Consistency

Two competing patterns exist:

```javascript
// Pattern A (newer): Structured result helpers
return actionSuccess({ purchase });     // { success: true, data: ... }
return actionFailure('CODE', 'message'); // { success: false, error: ..., code: ... }

// Pattern B (legacy): Direct objects
return { success: true, terminals: result.rows };
return { success: false, error: error.message };
```

**Impact:** Frontend must handle both response shapes, leading to inconsistent error handling.

