# PHASE 4: Business Logic Validation

## 4.1 POS Sale Flow Analysis

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant UI as POS UI
    participant SA as Server Action
    participant DB as PostgreSQL
    participant Stock as Stock Pipeline
    participant GL as GL Engine

    UI->>SA: createPosTransactionAction(data)
    SA->>DB: BEGIN
    SA->>DB: Validate session is open
    SA->>DB: Generate TX number (MAX + 1)
    SA->>DB: INSERT pos_transactions
    loop For each item
        SA->>DB: INSERT pos_transaction_items
        SA->>Stock: removeStockAction (warehouse + batch + serial)
    end
    loop For each payment
        SA->>DB: INSERT pos_payments
    end
    SA->>GL: createGLEntryAction (debit Cash, credit Revenue)
    SA->>DB: COMMIT
    SA-->>UI: { success, transaction }
```

### Findings

| Check | Status | Details |
|-------|--------|---------|
| Stock deduction | ✅ | Uses `removeStockAction` pipeline |
| Tax calculation | ✅ | Per-item tax with `Math.round` |
| Discount logic | ✅ | Per-item discount amount |
| Payment reconciliation | ⚠️ | No validation that payment total ≥ grand total |
| GL entry creation | ✅ | Double-entry with Cash/Card split |
| Cash drawer tracking | ✅ | Session open/close with reconciliation |
| Audit trail | ✅ | `auditWrite` fire-and-forget |
| **TX number generation** | 🔴 | **Race condition: `MAX + 1` is not concurrency-safe** |

> [!CAUTION]
> **Transaction number generation** uses `SELECT MAX(...) + 1` which is vulnerable to race conditions under concurrent POS terminals. Two simultaneous sales could generate the same number. Use a PostgreSQL `SEQUENCE` or `advisory lock` instead.

## 4.2 Purchase Flow Analysis

| Check | Status | Details |
|-------|--------|---------|
| Duplicate PO check | ✅ | Checks before insert |
| GRN (Goods Receipt) | ✅ | Stock added only when status = 'received' |
| Batch auto-creation | ✅ | Creates batch if `batch_number` provided |
| Inventory increment | ✅ | Uses `addStockAction` pipeline |
| GL entry (purchase) | ✅ | Debit Inventory, Credit AP |
| Vendor balance update | ✅ | Increments `outstanding_balance` |
| Cost recalculation | 🔴 | **No FIFO/weighted average cost update** |
| Idempotency guard | ⚠️ | Status check prevents double-receive, but no idempotency key |

> [!WARNING]
> **Cost recalculation is missing.** When a purchase is received, the product's `cost_price` is NOT updated with weighted average or FIFO logic. This means inventory valuation reports will use stale cost data.

## 4.3 Inventory Adjustments

| Check | Status | Details |
|-------|--------|---------|
| Manual adjustments | ✅ | `adjustStockAction` |
| Damage/expiry | ⚠️ | Generic adjustment, no specific damage tracking |
| Stock transfer | ✅ | Full from/to warehouse with `stock_transfers` table |
| GL entry on adjustment | ✅ | Via `AccountingService.recordBusinessTransaction('stock_adjustment')` |
| Reservation system | ✅ | `inventory_reservations` with TTL |

## 4.4 Accounting Integrity

| Check | Status | Details |
|-------|--------|---------|
| Double-entry enforcement | ✅ | [createGLEntryAction](file:///c:/Users/zaliz/Downloads/APP_CHAT/financial-hub/lib/actions/basic/accounting.js#102-237) validates `debit == credit` (0.01 tolerance) |
| Fiscal period guard | ✅ | `checkFiscalPeriodOpen()` blocks entries in closed periods |
| Journal grouping | ✅ | All entries linked to parent `journal_entries` |
| Journal reversal | ✅ | `is_reversed` + `reversed_by` on journal_entries |
| Period locking | ✅ | `fiscal_periods.status = 'closed'` |
| System account protection | ✅ | Cannot delete/modify `is_system` accounts |
| **Trial balance verification** | 🔴 | **No automated check that total debits = total credits across all accounts** |

## 4.5 Concurrency & Race Conditions

| Risk | Severity | Location | Details |
|------|----------|----------|---------|
| TX number collision | 🔴 HIGH | POS, Invoices, Purchases, Journals | `MAX() + 1` pattern is not concurrency-safe |
| Stock overselling | 🟡 MEDIUM | `removeStockAction` | No `SELECT FOR UPDATE` or optimistic locking on stock |
| Double session close | ✅ LOW | POS sessions | Status check with transaction |
| Vendor balance drift | 🟡 MEDIUM | Purchase receipt | No `SELECT FOR UPDATE` on vendor row |

