# PHASE 6: Performance & Scalability

## 6.1 Query Performance Risks

| Risk | Severity | Location |
|------|----------|----------|
| N+1 on purchase items | 🟡 | [createPurchaseAction](file:///c:/Users/zaliz/Downloads/APP_CHAT/financial-hub/lib/actions/standard/purchase.js#121-286) loops `addStockAction` per item |
| `information_schema` query per request | 🔴 | [getPurchasesAction](file:///c:/Users/zaliz/Downloads/APP_CHAT/financial-hub/lib/actions/standard/purchase.js#13-61) checks column existence every call |
| `MAX()` aggregation on large tables | 🟡 | TX number generation scans full table |
| No cursor-based pagination | 🟡 | All list queries use OFFSET (degrades at scale) |
| GL account resolution per entry | 🟡 | [createGLEntryAction](file:///c:/Users/zaliz/Downloads/APP_CHAT/financial-hub/lib/actions/basic/accounting.js#102-237) does N queries to resolve account codes |

## 6.2 Connection Pool

| Setting | Value | Assessment |
|---------|-------|-----------|
| `max` | 30 | ⚠️ May exhaust on concurrent POS + web traffic |
| `idleTimeoutMillis` | 30000 | ✅ |
| `connectionTimeoutMillis` | 5000 | ✅ |
| `maxUses` | 7500 | ✅ Good for preventing memory leaks |

## 6.3 Caching Strategy

**Current state: NO caching layer exists.** Every request hits the database.

**Recommended caching targets:**
- GL account code → ID mappings (used in every financial transaction)
- Business plan tier (queried on every guarded action)
- Tenant settings / configuration
- Product catalog for POS terminals

## 6.4 Scaling Recommendations

| Recommendation | Priority | Impact |
|----------------|----------|--------|
| Add Redis/Upstash cache layer | 🔴 HIGH | 60%+ reduction in DB queries |
| Replace `MAX()+1` with PostgreSQL sequences | 🔴 HIGH | Eliminates race conditions |
| Implement cursor-based pagination | 🟡 MEDIUM | Scalable list queries |
| Move audit logging to async queue | 🟡 MEDIUM | Reduces transaction latency |
| Add read replica for reports | 🟢 LOW | Separates OLTP/OLAP workloads |

