# PHASE 8: Reporting Output

## 8.1 Critical Fix Priority List

### 🔴 HIGH Priority (Fix Immediately)

| # | Issue | Impact | Location |
|---|-------|--------|----------|
| 1 | **12 child tables missing `business_id`** | Cross-tenant data leakage | Schema-wide |
| 2 | **RBAC not enforced on most server actions** | Any member can perform any action | `lib/actions/basic/*`, `lib/actions/standard/*` |
| 3 | **Race condition on TX number generation** | Duplicate transaction numbers | POS, Invoice, Purchase, Journal |
| 4 | **No rate limiting** | Brute-force, DoS vulnerability | Global (missing middleware) |
| 5 | **Column name mismatches** (Prisma vs SQL) | Runtime errors | [pos.js](file:///c:/Users/zaliz/Downloads/APP_CHAT/financial-hub/lib/api/pos.js), potentially others |
| 6 | **No FIFO/avg cost recalculation** | Incorrect inventory valuation | Purchase flow |

### 🟡 MEDIUM Priority (Fix Within 2 Weeks)

| # | Issue | Impact | Location |
|---|-------|--------|----------|
| 7 | Missing `updated_by` on financial tables | Compliance gap | gl_entries, journal_entries |
| 8 | Payment total not validated against grand total | Over/under payments undetected | POS checkout |
| 9 | `information_schema` queried per request | Performance degradation | [purchase.js](file:///c:/Users/zaliz/Downloads/APP_CHAT/financial-hub/lib/actions/standard/purchase.js) |
| 10 | No caching layer | Unnecessary DB load | Global |
| 11 | Inconsistent response structure | Frontend complexity | Across all actions |
| 12 | Audit logging fire-and-forget | Silent audit failures | `auditWrite` |
| 13 | No optimistic locking on stock | Race conditions | `removeStockAction` |
| 14 | GL account code→ID lookup per entry | N+1 in financial operations | [createGLEntryAction](file:///c:/Users/zaliz/Downloads/APP_CHAT/financial-hub/lib/actions/basic/accounting.js#102-237) |
| 15 | No bulk export functionality | Missing enterprise feature | All entities |

### 🟢 LOW Priority (Roadmap Items)

| # | Issue | Impact | Location |
|---|-------|--------|----------|
| 16 | No event-driven architecture | Limited async capabilities | Architecture |
| 17 | No WebSocket for real-time | No live POS/KDS updates | Architecture |
| 18 | No API webhooks | No external integrations | Architecture |
| 19 | Cursor-based pagination | Scale limitation | List queries |
| 20 | Multi-currency transactions | International market | Invoice/POS |

## 8.2 Refactoring Roadmap

### Phase 1: Security Hardening (Week 1-2)
1. Add `business_id` to all 12 child tables + migration
2. Migrate ALL server actions to use [withGuard()](file:///c:/Users/zaliz/Downloads/APP_CHAT/financial-hub/lib/rbac/serverGuard.js#31-172) pattern
3. Add Next.js middleware with rate limiting (Upstash `@upstash/ratelimit`)
4. Replace `MAX()+1` with PostgreSQL sequences for all document numbers
5. Add `updated_by` column to financial tables

### Phase 2: Data Integrity (Week 3-4)
6. Implement FIFO/weighted average cost engine
7. Add optimistic locking (`version` column) on products, stock, vendor/customer balances
8. Validate payment total ≥ grand total on POS checkout
9. Cache GL account code→ID mappings (Redis or in-memory LRU)
10. Standardize all action response shapes to `actionSuccess` / `actionFailure`

### Phase 3: Performance (Week 5-6)
11. Add Redis/Upstash cache for plan tiers, business settings, product catalogs
12. Replace `information_schema` runtime checks with static configuration
13. Implement cursor-based pagination on all list endpoints
14. Batch GL account lookups (use [getGLAccountsByTypes](file:///c:/Users/zaliz/Downloads/APP_CHAT/financial-hub/lib/actions/basic/accounting.js#61-101) consistently)

### Phase 4: Enterprise Features (Week 7-10)
15. Implement bulk CSV/Excel export on all entities
16. Add multi-currency support to invoices and POS
17. Build webhook dispatch system
18. Implement recurring invoices
19. Add stock take / physical count module
20. Build e-invoicing integration (FBR Pakistan)

